items.title: Indians can tie MLB record with 21 straight wins
items.summary: The Indians have already made history, and they will aim to do it again this afternoon, live on MLB.TV and MLB Network at noon ET. Cleveland will look to tie the 1935 Cubs for the modern baseball record of 21 straight victories.
items.content: The Indians have already made history, and they will aim to do it again this afternoon, live on MLB.TV and MLB Network at noon ET. Cleveland will look to tie the 1935 Cubs for the modern baseball record of 21 straight victories.

items.title: Path to the Postseason: Sept. 12
items.summary: The 5-3 win over the Giants punched the Dodgers ticket to the postseason, guaranteeing them at least a Wild Card spot as they chase a sixth-consecutive National League West title. It was a long time coming for the Dodgers, who still own the best record in baseball but have seen their hold on that position slip in recent weeks by losing 16 of their last 18 games.

items.summary: Indians manager Terry Francona discusses Corey Kluber's shutout in Cleveland's 20th straight victory, which ties an AL record.

items.summary: The Indians can make modern baseball history this afternoon at Progressive Field as they go for their 21st consecutive victory, and fans can watch all the drama streaming live on MLB.TV or on MLB Network.

items.title: McCullers scratched from start with arm fatigue
items.summary: Astros right-hander Lance McCullers Jr., who came off the disabled list Wednesday in Seattle in his first start in more than month, was scratched from his scheduled start Wednesday against the Angels with what manager A.J. Hinch called "arm fatigue."
